result.execSummary:
The defendant James E. Penrod Jr. was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

superMiscConds.notes: If probation or extended supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.  This applies to all counts and financial obligations.

Obey all of the rules and regulations of supervising probation agent.
*  Pay supervision fees.
Do not possess or consume alcoholic beverages and do not have alcoholic beverages within the residence.  Do not possess or consume controlled substances, except by prescription.  Submit voluntarily to random tests of blood, breath or urine.  Participate in counseling deemed appropriate by agent.  Counseling shall specifically include:  AODA Assessment and follow through with recommended treatment.  Actively search for employment, be employed or attend an educational institution or vocational training program.
*  Pay fine of $400.00 and court costs including all applicable surcharges.
*  DE is ordered to submit to a DNA sample & pay DNA surcharge and notice is given.
May not have contact with Maureen C A (dob 8/12/75) or her residence, unless otherwise permitted by the court/agent.  Sex offender evaluation required.

Attorney Jason Zapf appeared for the State. DE appears in custody with Atty Diane Caspari. Victim present in court.   Clerk P. Scypta.   
MINUTES: 1116 -   State is compliant with victim rights notification.  Victim statement with KHDS representative, Karen Annan.   Sentence recommendations made.  Defendant is sentenced to 4 years in the WSP; 2 years Initial Confinement followed by 2 years of Extended Supervision.  DE (is) eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program. Sex offender evaluation ordered. 221 days credit.  DE is ordered to submit to a DNA sample & pay $250 DNA surcharge and notice is given. $400 fine plus court costs ordered. No extradition costs incurred from DE's transfer from IL.  Appeal Rights, Firearm Warning & Voting Acknowledgement and Conditions of Extended Supervision given. (ps 12/10/15)
